td-5c44d7: Limit default loading of account HMAC keys
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P1
Labels: review-finding, security

Description:
Account records currently include hmac_key in default queries, and those structs are passed through general account-loading paths (app/lib/app/accounts/account.ex:17, app/lib/app/accounts.ex:303, app/lib/app/accounts.ex:329, app/lib/app/account_context.ex:20, app/lib/app_web/plugs/load_account.ex:21). This broadens secret exposure beyond the dedicated key accessor and increases leak risk through future serialization or logging paths. Suggested fix: mark hmac_key as not loaded by default and require explicit select in narrow code paths that truly need it.

Acceptance Criteria:
1) Default account fetch/list paths no longer load hmac_key. 2) GA.Accounts.get_hmac_key/1 still returns the key for valid accounts. 3) Tests assert hmac_key is absent in normal account context loads and only available via explicit key retrieval.

