td-e67550: Validate account_id in get_hmac_key/1
Status: [in_progress]
Type: bug | Priority: P2
Labels: review-finding, code-quality, testing

Description:
GA.Accounts.get_hmac_key/1 builds a query directly from account_id without an upfront UUID cast (app/lib/app/accounts.ex:342-346). A malformed ID can raise Ecto.Query.CastError instead of returning a tagged error, making caller behavior inconsistent and potentially crashing request paths that pass unsanitized values. Suggested fix: cast with Ecto.UUID.cast/1 first and return {:error, :not_found} or {:error, :invalid_id} for bad input.

Acceptance Criteria:
1) get_hmac_key/1 handles malformed IDs without raising. 2) Function returns documented tagged errors for bad or missing IDs. 3) Tests cover malformed UUID input and assert no exception is raised.

