td-82a6f0: Optimize HMAC backfill migration for large account sets
Status: [in_progress]
Type: chore | Priority: P3
Labels: review-finding, performance

Description:
Migration backfill currently executes one UPDATE per account row after selecting all IDs (app/priv/repo/migrations/20260303144500_add_hmac_key_to_accounts.exs:26-33). This is functionally correct but scales poorly and can prolong migration lock time on larger datasets. Suggested fix: use a set-based SQL update or batched strategy that reduces round-trips while preserving cryptographic randomness guarantees.

Acceptance Criteria:
1) Backfill strategy avoids one UPDATE per row for large datasets. 2) Keys remain unique, 32-byte binaries after migration. 3) Migration documentation/comments explain the chosen performance-safe approach.

